1
00:01:18,470 --> 00:01:19,470
My daughter...

2
00:01:21,570 --> 00:01:23,240
Please save my daughter, Min Seo.

3
00:01:30,310 --> 00:01:31,350
I...

4
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,320
I'm begging you.

5
00:01:38,420 --> 00:01:40,360
Hey, what are you doing, Counselor?

6
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,670
I'll save her, Counselor.

7
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:56,840
But I need a favor in return.

8
00:01:58,570 --> 00:02:00,540
What? Professor Han?

9
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:02,150
Yes.

10
00:02:03,580 --> 00:02:06,520
He's either dead or being held captive.
It has to be one or the other.

11
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:09,350
I was supposed to meet him
at two o'clock today,

12
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:11,420
but he never showed up.

13
00:02:12,290 --> 00:02:13,290
Why?

14
00:02:13,690 --> 00:02:15,690
Professor Han said he would help me.

15
00:02:16,830 --> 00:02:18,090
To get me out of here.

16
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:21,830
Get out of here?

17
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,740
We have three minutes left.

18
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,970
From now on, you do exactly as I say.

19
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:34,480
I promise you,
I will make sure Min Seo gets treated.

20
00:02:36,410 --> 00:02:38,310
In Professor Han's place,

21
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,950
you're going to help me get out of here.

22
00:02:42,220 --> 00:02:46,120
I need you to trust me again,
just like you did at the trial.

23
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:48,290
(The Mobius Strip)

24
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:51,060
(Current Affairs Takedown)

25
00:02:56,370 --> 00:02:58,130
Min Gyeong, let's get some chicken.

26
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,900
- Reporter Jo, come look at this.
- If it's not urgent, let's eat first.

27
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,410
I'm telling you. Get over here now!

28
00:03:03,710 --> 00:03:06,710
I spent all day looking for people
who knew Lee Gyu Hyeong...

29
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:09,080
and went straight to the Guam police.
I haven't eaten anything.

30
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:12,780
What? What's this? Chaeum?

31
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,720
- Say something.
- Be quiet for a second.

32
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:19,860
- Why?
- I've got it. That feeling.

33
00:03:21,460 --> 00:03:23,660
I can smell an exclusive.

34
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:28,870
Check if any political funds were funneled
from Chaeum to Assemblyman Baek.

35
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:34,140
I'm going after Chairman Chae Jeong Su,
son of Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

36
00:03:35,070 --> 00:03:36,710
It's time to put him under the microscope.

37
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:43,350
You've got some nerve.

38
00:03:44,450 --> 00:03:47,750
What were you doing
meeting with Lee Woo Gyeom?

39
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,690
Let Woo Gyeom go.

40
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,660
You must have seen it in the notes.

41
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:55,160
If we want to develop the cure,

42
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,660
we have to stop his treatments
immediately.

43
00:03:58,830 --> 00:04:01,160
If you keep recklessly
using him like this,

44
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:05,130
all the research your father and I did
could go down the drain.

45
00:04:05,970 --> 00:04:07,340
How much more can he take?

46
00:04:08,170 --> 00:04:09,440
His body, I mean.

47
00:04:10,370 --> 00:04:11,940
According to his own calculations,

48
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,680
ten people.

49
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,710
No. Even ten would be pushing it.

50
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:18,210
I don't know the exact details,

51
00:04:18,410 --> 00:04:22,690
but the more blood they draw,
the more his body changes, Chairman Chae!

52
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:25,690
We have to pull him out of circulation
immediately.

53
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:29,590
We may never find another test subject
like him in our lifetime,

54
00:04:29,690 --> 00:04:31,090
and it's unlikely another one
will ever appear.

55
00:04:31,690 --> 00:04:34,630
I'll help you.
To mass produce the cure you want so much.

56
00:04:37,830 --> 00:04:42,100
Why don't we just drain all of his blood
before his condition changes?

57
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,440
What? If we do that...

58
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:48,280
Don't tell me you're actually worried
about Lee Woo Gyeom.

59
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:49,810
No. That's not it.

60
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:54,120
Is it your obsession with
your life's work, then?

61
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:58,220
Whatever the case,

62
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:02,490
you're quite something, Professor.

63
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:07,930
Your years of hard work
and dedication to Chaeum...

64
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,370
I will never forget them.

65
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,970
Give my father my regards.

66
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,920
Director Ahn.

67
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:32,590
Since it's come to this,
stage the scene well.

68
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,460
It's business as usual for you, isn't it?

69
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:38,530
Yes, Chairman.
I'll take care of it quietly.

70
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:40,230
Good.

71
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:47,300
Hey, get this out of here. Now.

72
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,250
Welcome, Your Excellency.

73
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,990
"Your Excellency?" Give me a break.

74
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:06,590
Have a seat.

75
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:14,630
An aide in the Republic of Korea
must be paid quite well.

76
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:16,030
Decent? Hardly.

77
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:19,870
With my son starting middle school,
things are getting tight.

78
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:23,040
For someone with tight finances,
this is a lavish spread, don't you think?

79
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:25,270
Did Assemblyman Baek arrange this?

80
00:06:26,910 --> 00:06:28,310
Or is this a case of...

81
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:32,210
"When the cat's away, the mice will play?"

82
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:36,790
So blunt and righteous.
You really haven't changed a bit.

83
00:06:37,590 --> 00:06:38,820
This is all wild-caught.

84
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:44,060
- Please, enjoy the food and have a drink.
- Let's skip the empty pleasantries.

85
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:45,630
Just get to the point.

86
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:50,770
Very well.

87
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:55,370
Prosecutor, why are you so obsessed
with the Lee Woo Gyeom case?

88
00:06:58,610 --> 00:07:00,540
I should be asking you the same thing,
Chief Pyo.

89
00:07:01,410 --> 00:07:04,050
Why are you so obsessed with my case?

90
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:10,120
The trial's already over,
so it's not your case anymore, is it?

91
00:07:11,450 --> 00:07:12,820
Let's stop playing word games.

92
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,590
And let's be honest with each other.

93
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,330
The other day,
when you came to my office...

94
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,530
Why did you leak that information about...

95
00:07:21,530 --> 00:07:23,530
Professor Han experimenting
on Lee Woo Gyeom?

96
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,540
While Lee Woo Gyeom was in a coma...

97
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:31,440
Did you know Professor Han used him
as a research subject?

98
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:32,940
Where did you get that information?

99
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:37,150
Where it came from isn't important.
What matters is that before you knew,

100
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:42,690
someone had already taken care of things
regarding Lee Woo Gyeom.

101
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,790
It's no big deal, really.

102
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:52,500
A man has got to make a living.

103
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,330
When the cat's away, the mice should play,
don't you think?

104
00:08:02,410 --> 00:08:03,670
So, you're saying...

105
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:07,510
you want to take down Assemblyman Baek,
and you're going to use me to do it?

106
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:09,580
"Use you?"

107
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:13,080
I distinctly told you not to dig too deep.

108
00:08:13,650 --> 00:08:16,390
- You're the one who wouldn't stop.
- Assemblyman Baek...

109
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,790
How involved is he in Professor Han's
illegal medical practices?

110
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:21,260
Before we get to that,

111
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:24,460
shouldn't your promise to ensure my safety
come first?

112
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:40,840
Fine, whatever...

113
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:42,750
I might as well hear...

114
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:44,380
how you intend to use me.

115
00:08:46,350 --> 00:08:48,680
It's a very long story.

116
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:51,520
You've been looking at this the wrong way
from the very beginning, Prosecutor.

117
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:52,920
What do you mean?

118
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:55,990
This whole thing didn't start
with Lee Woo Gyeom.

119
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:58,460
What?

120
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,560
Chairman Chae Jeong Su's father,
Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

121
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,370
You have to trace it all the way back
to Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

122
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,200
It's a pleasure.

123
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,770
Chairman Chae Jeong Su.

124
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,510
What did you want to see me about?

125
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,680
I wanted to thank you.

126
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,680
Thanks to your support,

127
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,880
I'm able to treat patients...

128
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,780
in this wonderful environment.

129
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:05,190
"Wonderful environment?"

130
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:08,120
You're a real piece of work,
Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

131
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,800
You're back to being monitored
twenty-four seven,

132
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,570
just another test subject.

133
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:18,970
Are you really okay with that?

134
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:23,140
That's a bit harsh.

135
00:11:24,610 --> 00:11:28,480
Calling a living person
a "test subject" to their face.

136
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:33,520
A while ago, you took my notes...

137
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,650
from Professor Han, didn't you?

138
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:42,930
Don't tell me you wasted your time
trying to understand them.

139
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:52,130
Did you really think you could
achieve something...

140
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:55,500
that medical professionals
worldwide couldn't?

141
00:11:58,110 --> 00:12:00,810
You're awfully generous with yourself.

142
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:06,980
Mr. Chairman.

143
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:11,520
You can't mass-produce the cure
without me.

144
00:12:15,690 --> 00:12:18,190
I've already seen the notes, so I'm aware.

145
00:12:19,330 --> 00:12:22,970
- That's why we brought you to Chaeum...
- I have a question.

146
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,830
I still have my blood, don't I?

147
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,910
Can my blood be used to cure
incurable diseases forever?

148
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:32,340
What do you mean?

149
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:37,010
Every time I give blood for patients,
my body generates new blood.

150
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:42,080
The new blood my body generates...
Will it contain the cure or not?

151
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:45,550
Go ahead, tell me.

152
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:47,920
This is your only chance for an answer.

153
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,860
It must.

154
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:56,130
How else could you have treated
so many patients until now?

155
00:12:58,130 --> 00:12:59,440
Here's a more interesting question.

156
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:04,840
What percentage of the cure
is in my blood right now?

157
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:08,280
And I'll be drawing blood
for the rest of my life.

158
00:13:08,540 --> 00:13:11,050
Will the potency of the cure
diminish each time?

159
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:14,450
Will it remain stable? Or...

160
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,220
will it disappear completely?

161
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,460
Chairman Chae.

162
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:27,060
Do you still see me
as just a test subject?

163
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:32,100
I'm the one running the experiment here.

164
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:35,600
Everyone who wanted a piece of me,
including you...

165
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:39,240
are all just test subjects
in my research. All 17 of them.

166
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:42,240
My test subjects who failed
to serve their purpose.

167
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,280
You remember how they died, don't you?

168
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:53,290
So, Chairman...

169
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:57,230
You and I need to play nice.

170
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:01,030
If I were to fail this treatment
with the whole world watching,

171
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:05,170
what would happen to Chaeum?

172
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:07,240
You know full well what would.

173
00:14:16,450 --> 00:14:18,950
I'm reporting live in front of
Hana Hospital where Lee Woo Gyeom...

174
00:14:19,050 --> 00:14:22,550
is set to begin his 3rd treatment
for his 1st outpatient session.

175
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:27,920
The patient, Jeon Seung Hun,
has both Crohn's disease and hemophilia,

176
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,360
making his case extremely rare.

177
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:33,230
As a result, a massive crowd of reporters
has gathered here today,

178
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,300
creating a complete media circus.

179
00:14:38,870 --> 00:14:43,070
- Mom.
- Citizens who trust Lee Woo Gyeom...

180
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:47,710
and citizens praying for the patient,
have begun to gather.

181
00:14:48,210 --> 00:14:51,050
At this moment, a mix of anxiety and hope
hangs in the air.

182
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:53,420
All eyes are fixed on one thing.

183
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:57,890
Lee Woo Gyeom
and the potential for a miracle.

184
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:05,430
Chaeum Medical's stock has been hitting
its daily limit for several days in a row,

185
00:15:05,490 --> 00:15:07,400
drawing keen interest from the market.

186
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:11,630
This recent surge comes amid
a mix of hope and concern,

187
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:16,510
as all watch if Lee Woo Gyeom's blood
could be the next medical breakthrough.

188
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,510
(HBN Today)

189
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:19,810
(Lee Woo Gyeom's 3rd Patient:
Jeon Seung Hun)

190
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:20,940
(Baek Proposes the Lee Woo Gyeom Act)

191
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:26,320
(Officer Lee Hye In)

192
00:15:30,350 --> 00:15:31,690
(Lee Woo Gyeom's 3rd Patient:
Jeon Seung Hun)

193
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:32,860
(Baek Proposes the Lee Woo Gyeom Act)

194
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,160
(Chaeum Medical's Stock Keeps Rising)

195
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:37,130
Prosecutor, we're ready. Let's go.

196
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:39,860
It's Lee Woo Gyeom!

197
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:44,000
(Ministry of Justice)

198
00:15:44,970 --> 00:15:46,740
- It's Lee Woo Gyeom!
- Lee Woo Gyeom!

199
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:47,970
- A word, please!
- Lee Woo Gyeom!

200
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:50,210
- How's the patient?
- About today...

201
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:54,140
(Medical Demonstration Venue)

202
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:57,250
- Mr. Lee!
- Just one word, please!

203
00:15:58,710 --> 00:15:59,720
Over here, please!

204
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,340
Got it.

205
00:16:24,270 --> 00:16:25,270
Right.

206
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:27,080
Yes.

207
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,550
I'm swamped.
Why did you all have to show up in a pack?

208
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:38,550
Prosecutor, you've been approaching
this all wrong from the beginning.

209
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:40,390
What do you mean?

210
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:43,530
This whole thing didn't start
with Lee Woo Gyeom.

211
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:45,260
What?

212
00:16:45,260 --> 00:16:47,460
Chairman Chae Jeong Su's father,
Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

213
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,070
You have to trace it all the way back
to Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

214
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:58,240
(2022 National Assembly Audit Report)

215
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:04,750
Officer Lee, Chief Bang.

216
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:08,780
I need the two of you to start
by going over the Chaeum audit reports.

217
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:11,850
Go meet the former employees
of the Chaeum Research Institute...

218
00:17:12,050 --> 00:17:13,260
and gather information.

219
00:17:13,260 --> 00:17:16,120
Do you remember what kind of treatments
the patients received back then?

220
00:17:17,190 --> 00:17:20,200
I remember that most patients
were hospitalized long-term.

221
00:17:20,430 --> 00:17:24,000
These treatments weren't approved,
were they?

222
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:25,100
- No.
- No.

223
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:28,270
- You mean Dr. Song Min Su?
- He was a young and very capable doctor.

224
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:31,910
Do you know what kind of research
the two of them were conducting?

225
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:37,250
As I recall, even within Chaeum,
Professor Han's project was kept secret.

226
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,480
Kept secret?

227
00:17:39,510 --> 00:17:41,320
Though their identity was never revealed,

228
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:45,450
it began with a tip from a whistleblower
at the Chaeum Research Institute.

229
00:17:45,990 --> 00:17:49,220
Chaeum forged surgical consent forms
for patients with no next of kin.

230
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:51,760
When a patient died during surgery,
the prosecution filed charges,

231
00:17:51,830 --> 00:17:53,530
and after the trial,
it even led to a national audit.

232
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:56,530
The prosecutor on the case at the time
was Oh Hyeon Deuk.

233
00:17:56,770 --> 00:18:00,100
The district attorney who approved it
was the current Assemblyman Baek Sang Hwa.

234
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,940
And the person who performed the surgery
and testified at the National Assembly...

235
00:18:04,270 --> 00:18:06,310
was the late Dr. Song Min Su.

236
00:18:12,050 --> 00:18:13,780
(2022 Chaeum Medical Center
National Assembly Audit Report)

237
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,890
- What is this?
- The case you handled.

238
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:20,660
Professor Han's illegal medical practices
case from 2022.

239
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:23,290
And everything related to...

240
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:25,630
the Chaeum Medical's
National Assembly audit...

241
00:18:25,790 --> 00:18:27,600
Assemblyman Baek, the DA at the time,

242
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,870
ordered you to give them
a slap on the wrist...

243
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,500
and wrap it up, didn't he?

244
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:36,470
That case was closed a long time ago.

245
00:18:36,970 --> 00:18:39,370
Closed? But Lee Woo Gyeom, that monster,

246
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:41,940
- he was a product of all this.
- Hey, Cha Yi Yeon!

247
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,650
What on earth happened back then?

248
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:46,780
Drop it.

249
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:50,250
If you keep digging into this case...

250
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:51,490
You think it's just me
and Assemblyman Baek...

251
00:18:51,490 --> 00:18:52,490
who will go down?

252
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:57,030
If you push this any further,
it'll be your neck on the line too!

253
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:09,340
What is it?

254
00:19:10,340 --> 00:19:11,410
It's Min Gyeong.

255
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,310
Sorry to interrupt.

256
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:16,410
So are we working with Prosecutor Cha now?

257
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:19,920
If Prosecutor Cha needs anything,
give her whatever help she needs.

258
00:19:29,990 --> 00:19:33,060
That's not going to happen.

259
00:19:35,730 --> 00:19:36,730
(Baek's Misconduct: Han Sang Ho Case)

260
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,470
Assemblyman Baek used
his friend's father's name...

261
00:19:39,530 --> 00:19:42,870
to create a shell company
and raise campaign funds.

262
00:19:44,570 --> 00:19:47,180
As his junior, didn't you think
that was a little pathetic, Director Oh?

263
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:52,780
The person who worked with Detective Gong
before the investigative authority split.

264
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,520
It turns out to be Prosecutor Cha's boss.

265
00:19:54,580 --> 00:19:57,050
It turns out to be
Prosecutor Oh Hyeon Deuk...

266
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,720
who handled Professor Han's
malpractice case.

267
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:00,220
Prosecutor Oh Hyeon Deuk?

268
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,130
Okay, first, I'll...

269
00:20:03,730 --> 00:20:06,960
meet with Lee Woo Gyeom to find out more
about his mother, Kim Hye Joo's, death,

270
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:09,800
and find out more about Professor Han.

271
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:13,270
During the time of Professor Han's
illegal medical fraud case...

272
00:20:13,570 --> 00:20:15,700
Reporter Jo, I need you to dig into
what the people at Chaeum were up to.

273
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:19,040
Min Gyeong, you dig into
Assemblyman Baek's people.

274
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:20,680
Got it.

275
00:20:33,790 --> 00:20:37,530
Reporter Jo, I don't even know
where to begin.

276
00:20:38,390 --> 00:20:41,400
Keep digging, and something will turn up,
so don't worry too much.

277
00:20:43,230 --> 00:20:46,670
But what I need right now
are your real tricks of the trade.

278
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:50,610
You think you can solve this at your desk?
You've got to hit the pavement, like I do.

279
00:20:50,670 --> 00:20:52,210
(Attorney Park Mi Hyeon,
Chaeum Medical Center Counsel)

280
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:56,280
- Gosh, it's gorgeous.
- So beautiful.

281
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:57,510
So, so pretty.

282
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,940
Excuse me, how much longer?

283
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,640
We still have a long way to go.

284
00:21:24,770 --> 00:21:26,270
Just push through it.

285
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:30,580
All these interiors look the same
these days.

286
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,350
This is going to ruin my hair.

287
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:37,550
Find a new stylist at this place, got it?

288
00:21:38,290 --> 00:21:39,290
That'll be all.

289
00:21:43,530 --> 00:21:45,160
You get some real characters in here,
don't you?

290
00:21:46,490 --> 00:21:47,660
Here, let me throw that out for you.

291
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:06,550
(Oh Hyeon Deuk:
Suspect in Lee Woo Gyeom's Case)

292
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:10,590
(Baek Sang Hwa: Assemblyman for Guam)

293
00:22:15,690 --> 00:22:17,260
Hello, Prosecutor Cha.

294
00:22:18,390 --> 00:22:20,800
This is Yoon Min Gyeong.
We met a while ago.

295
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:22,830
Do you have a moment to talk?

296
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,070
Was ignoring Assemblyman Baek's corruption
and doing whatever he asked...

297
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:29,770
worth your current director position
and the promise of a secure future?

298
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,540
- Cha Yi Yeon! How dare you!
- Director Oh Hyeon Deuk!

299
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:36,480
From now on, I'm the one
who gets to do the shouting.

300
00:22:36,810 --> 00:22:38,580
- So you're going to listen.
- What?

301
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:41,580
If you want me to show you even an ounce
of respect as your junior,

302
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:44,950
approve the warrant right now,
you son of a gun.

303
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,640
(Emergency Medical Center)

304
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:47,850
(Family Waiting Room)

305
00:23:58,460 --> 00:24:00,460
(Radiology Department)

306
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:05,630
(Health Promotion Center)

307
00:24:18,650 --> 00:24:21,320
Keep this in mind.
Delay for even one second,

308
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:24,250
and all your long-laid plans
will come to nothing.

309
00:24:37,070 --> 00:24:38,070
(Assemblyman Baek Sang Hwa)

310
00:24:43,570 --> 00:24:44,570
Chief Pyo!

311
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:47,480
- Where's Chief Pyo?
- Sir, we need you to cooperate.

312
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:48,710
This little prick.

313
00:24:50,110 --> 00:24:53,750
Go get the Chief Prosecutor right now.
You don't know who I am?

314
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:58,720
I'm your senior. I'm Baek Sang Hwa,
Guam's 63rd Chief Prosecutor.

315
00:24:58,790 --> 00:25:03,690
Yes, we're aware. It's written right here,
Assemblyman Baek Sang Hwa.

316
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:05,830
Who's the prosecutor handling my case?

317
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:30,750
Counselor.

318
00:25:31,050 --> 00:25:34,890
I've hidden what you need to get out in
Building A's 3rd floor fire hose cabinet.

319
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:51,210
While I'm in the OR treating the patient,

320
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:55,340
I need you to go
to the place I told you about.

321
00:25:57,550 --> 00:26:00,220
If you stick to the route
I'm about to describe,

322
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:03,890
you'll be able to avoid the CCTV
and the security guards.

323
00:26:12,030 --> 00:26:13,230
(Current time)

324
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,180
(Current time)

325
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:31,350
At twelve o'clock sharp.

326
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,960
The second my surgery is finished,

327
00:26:45,130 --> 00:26:47,830
the power supply to the entire hospital
will be cut off,

328
00:26:48,630 --> 00:26:50,000
signaling the start of our plan,

329
00:26:51,730 --> 00:26:52,730
and all the lights...

330
00:26:54,940 --> 00:26:55,940
will go out.

331
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:01,540
What's going on?

332
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,310
- Is it a blackout? What's going on?
- What happened?

333
00:27:05,380 --> 00:27:07,080
- Is the power out downstairs too?
- Yes.

334
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,510
Four men at the entrance.
Team Two, lock down the corridors.

335
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:47,620
Others, follow me.

336
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:56,960
(Restricted area)

337
00:28:57,830 --> 00:29:00,330
- Why did the power go out suddenly?
- What's going on?

338
00:29:01,660 --> 00:29:02,900
See the patients first.

339
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:04,330
Yes, Doctor.

340
00:29:04,630 --> 00:29:06,330
- What happened?
- Right, understood.

341
00:29:13,510 --> 00:29:14,510
Be careful.

342
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:17,680
(Hana Hospital)

343
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:35,430
- Did anyone check the security office?
- When is the power coming back on?

344
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,370
This is a hospital! Why's the power out?

345
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:41,700
It's an emergency.
They should be fixing it right now!

346
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,100
Don't they have a backup generator?

347
00:30:18,470 --> 00:30:19,840
- Where did he go?
- Find him! Now!

348
00:30:19,910 --> 00:30:20,910
Head downstairs!

349
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:28,620
Lee Woo Gyeom's ankle monitor signal
was lost on sublevel two.

350
00:30:36,290 --> 00:30:37,830
- Find anything?
- Nothing yet, sir.

351
00:30:46,130 --> 00:30:47,500
- This way, sir.
- That way!

352
00:31:46,660 --> 00:31:48,600
It's been a while
since I've breathed fresh air.

353
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,270
But it's not as refreshing as I'd hoped.

354
00:32:02,940 --> 00:32:03,950
Darn it.

355
00:32:04,850 --> 00:32:07,450
- What is it?
- I think we're being followed.

356
00:32:17,830 --> 00:32:19,390
(Jo Woo Cheol, Daehan Ilbo News)

357
00:32:26,330 --> 00:32:28,700
- Yes, Mr. Park.
- Reporter Jo, where are you?

358
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:29,900
I'm over at Chaeum.

359
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,870
I'm going to do some digging
on Chairman Chae.

360
00:32:33,610 --> 00:32:37,010
Right. Okay, got it.

361
00:32:49,090 --> 00:32:50,190
What's going on?

362
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:51,830
That's the guy I saw
outside Professor Han's house.

363
00:33:30,460 --> 00:33:31,930
So, where are we heading now?

364
00:33:33,870 --> 00:33:34,870
For now...

365
00:33:44,750 --> 00:33:46,650
We will now begin the emergency briefing.

366
00:33:47,550 --> 00:33:49,120
Today at approximately 12:03 p.m.,

367
00:33:49,580 --> 00:33:51,350
Lee Woo Gyeom, who was being held
at the correctional center,

368
00:33:51,650 --> 00:33:55,490
escaped during an off-site medical visit,
breaching security.

369
00:33:56,290 --> 00:34:00,260
Serial killer Lee Woo Gyeom, once a medic
at the Chaeum Correctional Center,

370
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,500
has escaped during
an off-site medical appointment.

371
00:34:03,860 --> 00:34:06,530
The police are currently tracking
Lee Woo Gyeom's whereabouts.

372
00:34:11,870 --> 00:34:12,870
Are you okay?

373
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:43,840
Hey, look at me.

374
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:48,840
Are you all right?

375
00:34:51,050 --> 00:34:52,650
This wasn't part of the plan.

376
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:59,190
They're probably people from Chaeum.

377
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,020
They can't lay a hand on me anyway, so...

378
00:35:14,770 --> 00:35:17,610
Woo Gyeom. Stay put.

379
00:35:18,770 --> 00:35:19,770
Counselor.

380
00:35:24,250 --> 00:35:25,250
Hold on.

381
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:26,880
Wait a minute.

382
00:35:29,420 --> 00:35:30,420
You people...

383
00:35:31,190 --> 00:35:33,790
Do you have any idea
what you've just done?

384
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:35,920
Step aside, Counselor.

385
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:37,930
We're just here for Lee Woo Gyeom.

386
00:35:38,890 --> 00:35:39,890
You people.

387
00:35:40,390 --> 00:35:43,100
Why on earth are you doing this?

388
00:35:43,630 --> 00:35:46,830
- Do we need a reason to save a life?
- What?

389
00:35:52,310 --> 00:35:53,970
- Counselor!
- Reporter Jo.

390
00:35:59,010 --> 00:36:03,150
Are you all right?
Gosh, hold on. Wait, wait a minute.

391
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:04,790
Hold on.

392
00:36:05,550 --> 00:36:07,420
Woo Gyeom is hurt.
We need to move him, fast.

393
00:36:07,490 --> 00:36:10,320
I'll do my best to hold them off.
Take my car and get him out of here.

394
00:36:10,390 --> 00:36:11,390
Okay.

395
00:36:13,660 --> 00:36:14,660
Woo Gyeom, let's go.

396
00:36:15,700 --> 00:36:17,870
Hey, hold on. You can deal with me.

397
00:36:18,130 --> 00:36:21,170
- Why are you folks acting like this?
- Get him.

398
00:36:23,500 --> 00:36:26,670
- Hurry, get in.
- Come on.

399
00:36:27,610 --> 00:36:29,310
Gosh, it's been a while.

400
00:36:29,410 --> 00:36:31,450
I guess I'm about to punch some people
instead of typing with my keyboard.

401
00:36:58,970 --> 00:37:01,810
Gosh, you're good.

402
00:37:02,810 --> 00:37:04,450
Are you still having fun?

403
00:37:21,630 --> 00:37:23,660
Woo Gyeom. Hey, Woo Gyeom!

404
00:37:26,030 --> 00:37:27,330
We're almost there. Stay with me.

405
00:37:36,510 --> 00:37:37,850
Hey, Woo Gyeom.

406
00:37:38,950 --> 00:37:39,950
Come on, snap out of it. Let's get out.

407
00:37:40,650 --> 00:37:41,650
Let's go.

408
00:37:57,730 --> 00:37:59,330
Hey, hey. Get up.

409
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:01,540
Stay with me. Are you okay?

410
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:03,640
Come on.

411
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:16,080
Honey.

412
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,400
What took you so long?

413
00:38:33,530 --> 00:38:35,300
He got hurt. Can you check his wound?

414
00:38:36,140 --> 00:38:37,140
Oh, my.

415
00:38:49,750 --> 00:38:50,850
You must be Min Seo.

416
00:38:58,490 --> 00:39:02,400
Hey... Let's treat your wounds first.

417
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,330
Yes. Let's stop the bleeding first.

418
00:39:05,100 --> 00:39:06,100
Min Seo...

419
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,200
I need to treat Min Seo first.

420
00:40:42,030 --> 00:40:43,030
Min Seo.

421
00:40:58,050 --> 00:40:59,510
(Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon)

422
00:41:10,290 --> 00:41:11,390
Hey. Lee Woo Gyeom.

423
00:41:11,690 --> 00:41:13,990
- Lee Woo Gyeom!
- No!

424
00:41:21,940 --> 00:41:24,940
You were so confident.
What are you going to do now?

425
00:41:26,740 --> 00:41:30,680
The stock won't just be halved.
It'll be completely worthless.

426
00:41:31,910 --> 00:41:33,650
And forget about developing a cure.

427
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,120
Lee Woo Gyeom escaped.

428
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:40,450
Why did Prosecutor Cha raid Chaeum?

429
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:46,360
Chairman Chae Jeong Su.
Well? What's your excuse?

430
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:50,560
The son of a gun you were protecting
got hauled off by Prosecutor Cha.

431
00:41:51,730 --> 00:41:54,770
Did you forget that if you go down,
we go down with you?

432
00:41:55,340 --> 00:41:57,910
If you're holding something back,
spit it out now.

433
00:41:59,110 --> 00:42:01,540
I knew this would happen.

434
00:42:02,540 --> 00:42:05,550
A man who keeps a mere congressman
on a leash,

435
00:42:05,650 --> 00:42:08,380
and the dog itself. What's the difference?

436
00:42:09,380 --> 00:42:10,850
So undignified.

437
00:42:16,820 --> 00:42:17,830
Chairman Chae.

438
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,490
What are you going to do?

439
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:29,240
Just give me until the end of the day.

440
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:31,570
Once I get Lee Woo Gyeom back,

441
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:33,910
everything will go back to normal.

442
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:38,350
But is developing the cure even possible?

443
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,850
Come on.

444
00:42:42,620 --> 00:42:44,520
You should've handled things properly
from the get-go.

445
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:46,190
Mister.

446
00:42:50,220 --> 00:42:51,760
It's not like this costs us pocket change.

447
00:42:52,330 --> 00:42:54,730
In a situation like this,
do you really expect me to be polite?

448
00:42:58,370 --> 00:43:01,840
She asked if the cure's development
is a sure thing.

449
00:43:11,580 --> 00:43:12,610
You'll see when I get back.

450
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:15,180
I'll prove it right before your eyes.

451
00:43:20,550 --> 00:43:21,560
My goodness.

452
00:43:23,690 --> 00:43:25,630
What should we do
about Chairman Chae, sir?

453
00:43:27,090 --> 00:43:29,160
If you feel conflicted
because of your daughter,

454
00:43:29,430 --> 00:43:30,860
I can deal with Chairman Chae myself.

455
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,170
Don't you worry about it.

456
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:36,040
I'll handle this myself.

457
00:43:51,490 --> 00:43:53,490
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
